00:31.000 --> 00:34.000
The Isle of Sky

00:34.000 --> 00:39.000
Sky is an island off the northwest coast of Scotland.

00:39.000 --> 00:44.000
It is the largest and most well known of the inner hebrides,

00:44.000 --> 00:48.000
and many people think it looks like a big butterfly.

00:48.000 --> 00:53.000
It is 25 miles wide and 50 miles long,

00:54.000 --> 01:00.000
and it is often called, by its poetic name, Adlana Heo.

01:00.000 --> 01:06.000
Sky is famous for its natural beauty, history and wildlife.

01:06.000 --> 01:10.000
Climbers and walkers love going into the coolant hills,

01:10.000 --> 01:15.000
and on Sky you are never far from the sea.

01:15.000 --> 01:20.000
The wildlife ranges from magnificent golden eagle to red deer,

01:20.000 --> 01:26.000
and if you are lucky, you can see otters playing on the shores.

01:26.000 --> 01:31.000
As you travel around the island, it is possible to hear Scottish Gaelic,

01:31.000 --> 01:38.000
which is the local language, and you can find Gaelic culture everywhere.

01:38.000 --> 01:41.000
Sky is very beautiful.

01:41.000 --> 01:49.000
There are hillsides, locks, lakes, white washed cottages, lots of sheep,

01:49.000 --> 01:52.000
but almost no people.

01:52.000 --> 01:57.000
Many years ago, the inhabitants were Highland chieftains,

01:57.000 --> 02:01.000
lords or lairs who lived in castles,

02:01.000 --> 02:07.000
but now they are farmers or crafters and fishermen on the coasts.

02:07.000 --> 02:14.000
There are shopkeepers and teachers who live and work in the main towns of Broadford and Potry,

02:14.000 --> 02:18.000
but most people on Sky live simply.

02:18.000 --> 02:26.000
They are families who love the land of their fathers.

02:26.000 --> 02:31.000
Chapter 1 Meghan

02:31.000 --> 02:36.000
I pulled the curtains open and looked down at the street.

02:36.000 --> 02:43.000
It was hot, too hot for London in the middle of July, and I was angry.

02:43.000 --> 02:48.000
I closed the curtains and returned to my mother's room.

02:48.000 --> 02:52.000
She lay in bed, and I could hear her breathing.

02:52.000 --> 02:58.000
She looked so thin, and I sat next to her and held her hand.

02:58.000 --> 03:01.000
I'm not going, I said.

03:01.000 --> 03:04.000
You can't send me away.

03:04.000 --> 03:10.000
I looked at my mother, and her face was white like the sheets and pillowcases.

03:10.000 --> 03:15.000
It's only for a month, until I feel a little better, my darling.

03:15.000 --> 03:19.000
She said, then you can come home.

03:19.000 --> 03:23.000
Dr. Barnes stood on the other side of the bed.

03:23.000 --> 03:26.000
Has Meghan got any friends?

03:26.000 --> 03:30.000
He asked Mrs. Brown, our home help.

03:30.000 --> 03:33.000
Mrs. Brown shook her head.

03:33.000 --> 03:36.000
Meghan doesn't have any friends.

03:36.000 --> 03:38.000
I heard her whisper.

03:38.000 --> 03:41.000
She's a strange child.

03:41.000 --> 03:45.000
Friends? Of course I didn't have any friends.

03:45.000 --> 03:52.000
We moved to this part of London six months ago, and my new school was horrible.

03:52.000 --> 03:54.000
Mother didn't know.

03:54.000 --> 04:00.000
I didn't tell her about the bullies and the nasty text messages.

04:00.000 --> 04:03.000
Dr. Barnes put his glasses on.

04:03.000 --> 04:07.000
I could see that he didn't know what to do.

04:07.000 --> 04:10.000
We needed a miracle.

04:10.000 --> 04:13.000
Your mother is very unwell, Meghan.

04:13.000 --> 04:15.000
He said.

04:15.000 --> 04:20.000
She needs to rest, and you can't stay here for the summer holidays.

04:20.000 --> 04:23.000
I don't want to leave you, Mum.

04:23.000 --> 04:28.000
You want to send me to the Highlands of Scotland to stay with Uncle Fraser.

04:28.000 --> 04:31.000
But I hate the countryside.

04:31.000 --> 04:34.000
I stood up and looked at the doctor.

04:34.000 --> 04:39.000
I'm not going, and you can't make me go.

04:39.000 --> 04:42.000
But Dr. Barnes could make me go.

04:42.000 --> 04:44.000
And he did.

04:50.000 --> 04:56.000
I watched the countryside change through the window of the train as we travelled into Scotland.

04:56.000 --> 05:02.000
I could see fields, dry stone walls, and lots of sheep.

05:02.000 --> 05:06.000
But where were the people?

05:06.000 --> 05:11.000
Mrs. Wallace, a friend of Dr. Barnes was with me.

05:11.000 --> 05:15.000
She wanted to chat, but I didn't.

05:15.000 --> 05:18.000
The Isle of Skye is beautiful.

05:18.000 --> 05:22.000
The air is so fresh, she said.

05:22.000 --> 05:26.000
I hate fresh air. I like the air in London.

05:26.000 --> 05:28.000
I said.

05:28.000 --> 05:32.000
Mrs. Wallace sighed and opened her book.

05:32.000 --> 05:37.000
We changed trains, and the next one was very old.

05:37.000 --> 05:41.000
A man sat singing quietly in the corner.

05:41.000 --> 05:44.000
He had a long white beard.

05:44.000 --> 05:49.000
In another corner, there was a woman with a basket of chickens.

05:50.000 --> 05:52.000
I looked at these people.

05:52.000 --> 05:55.000
I came from a different world.

05:55.000 --> 06:01.000
In my world, there were shops, people, and traffic.

06:01.000 --> 06:04.000
We caught the ferry at Malik.

06:04.000 --> 06:11.000
The wind blew my long dark hair, and my pale blue eyes searched the island for people.

06:11.000 --> 06:14.000
But it looked so quiet.

06:14.000 --> 06:20.000
Cloud Island said Mrs. Wallace, giving me a sweet.

06:20.000 --> 06:25.000
In the old North language, ski means cloud.

06:25.000 --> 06:30.000
And I means island. It's often misty here.

06:30.000 --> 06:36.000
I didn't answer. I could only think that I wanted to go home.

06:36.000 --> 06:43.000
We caught off the ferry at Armadale, and I stood by the sea and waited for my uncle.

06:44.000 --> 06:47.000
I felt wrong in my London clothes.

06:47.000 --> 06:52.000
I took my mobile phone out of my pocket and called home.

06:52.000 --> 06:56.000
Mrs. Brown answered, but mum was asleep.

06:56.000 --> 07:01.000
Your uncle's here said Mrs. Wallace.

07:01.000 --> 07:03.000
I said goodbye.

07:03.000 --> 07:04.000
Meghan.

07:04.000 --> 07:07.000
A strong voice called.

07:07.000 --> 07:12.000
He was a tall man with wavy hair and a big smile.

07:12.000 --> 07:14.000
I'm over here.

07:14.000 --> 07:17.000
He disappeared behind some trees.

07:17.000 --> 07:20.000
Pulling my suitcase, I followed.

07:20.000 --> 07:23.000
But my uncle didn't have a car.

07:23.000 --> 07:27.000
He was standing next to a beige-coloured pony,

07:27.000 --> 07:32.000
and he put my suitcase into a little red trap.

