08:17.000 --> 08:19.000
Watched.

08:22.000 --> 08:24.000
Chapter Two.

08:24.000 --> 08:27.000
The Croft.

08:28.000 --> 08:31.000
The journey was uncomfortable in the pony and trap,

08:31.000 --> 08:34.000
as we trotted along the narrow roads.

08:34.000 --> 08:36.000
But it was fun too.

08:36.000 --> 08:40.000
I could see the bay, the seaweed and the rocks,

08:40.000 --> 08:43.000
and smell the salty sea.

08:43.000 --> 08:46.000
Sea gulls flew overhead.

08:46.000 --> 08:48.000
I looked at my uncle.

08:48.000 --> 08:50.000
He had my mother's smile,

08:50.000 --> 08:52.000
but they were very different.

08:52.000 --> 08:55.000
He saw me looking at him.

08:55.000 --> 08:59.000
So, this is your first visit to Skye Meghan.

08:59.000 --> 09:02.000
I'm so pleased you're here.

09:02.000 --> 09:03.000
He said,

09:03.000 --> 09:07.000
I want to bring Mum next time when she's better, I said.

09:07.000 --> 09:10.000
His eyes look sad.

09:10.000 --> 09:13.000
I want her to come here too.

09:13.000 --> 09:16.000
And then he took a deep breath,

09:16.000 --> 09:18.000
and there was silence.

09:18.000 --> 09:21.000
We trotted on through a forest,

09:21.000 --> 09:26.000
and then we stopped at a place where the view of the mountains was spectacular.

09:26.000 --> 09:28.000
The Kulin Range?

09:28.000 --> 09:30.000
Said Uncle Fraser.

09:30.000 --> 09:33.000
This is the best place to see the mountains.

09:33.000 --> 09:36.000
I got out of the trap and looked around.

09:36.000 --> 09:39.000
It was a magical place.

09:39.000 --> 09:43.000
There was a ruined castle and below a sandy beach.

09:43.000 --> 09:45.000
The waves crashed,

09:45.000 --> 09:50.000
and I thought I saw a silvery white horse playing in the water.

09:50.000 --> 09:52.000
It ran and jumped,

09:52.000 --> 09:55.000
and I am sure that I heard it call me.

09:55.000 --> 09:57.000
Uncle Fraser?

09:57.000 --> 09:59.000
I shouted.

09:59.000 --> 10:01.000
There's a white horse.

10:01.000 --> 10:03.000
He didn't hear me.

10:03.000 --> 10:05.000
And when I turned,

10:05.000 --> 10:08.000
the silvery white horse was not there.

10:08.000 --> 10:10.000
We got into the trap.

10:10.000 --> 10:14.000
I saw a silvery white horse down by the sea.

10:14.000 --> 10:15.000
I said,

10:15.000 --> 10:20.000
Uncle Fraser stopped and looked at me with surprise.

10:20.000 --> 10:21.000
Did you?

10:21.000 --> 10:23.000
But then he said no more.

10:23.000 --> 10:28.000
My mobile phone beeped.

10:28.000 --> 10:31.000
You have one new message, it said.

10:31.000 --> 10:34.000
I pressed, read.

10:34.000 --> 10:37.000
Have a sad holiday.

10:37.000 --> 10:39.000
I pressed eliminate.

10:39.000 --> 10:43.000
It was from one of the horrible girls at school.

10:43.000 --> 10:45.000
I switched my phone off.

10:45.000 --> 10:48.000
I needed to forget about them.

10:48.000 --> 10:51.000
The roads were very narrow now.

10:51.000 --> 10:53.000
We are nearly home.

10:53.000 --> 10:55.000
Said my uncle.

10:55.000 --> 10:57.000
I stared at him.

10:57.000 --> 10:59.000
We couldn't be nearly home.

10:59.000 --> 11:02.000
We were in the countryside.

11:02.000 --> 11:04.000
I could see some small houses,

11:04.000 --> 11:06.000
lots of animals and grass,

11:06.000 --> 11:09.000
but there was no town.

11:09.000 --> 11:13.000
Uncle Fraser turned right into a small track.

11:13.000 --> 11:15.000
Home, Darwin?

11:15.000 --> 11:18.000
Uncle Fraser said to the pony.

11:18.000 --> 11:20.000
Darwin walked slowly

11:20.000 --> 11:23.000
because there were chickens running in front of him.

11:23.000 --> 11:25.000
At the end of the track,

11:25.000 --> 11:30.000
there was a little white house with a front garden full of flowers.

11:30.000 --> 11:31.000
In one field,

11:31.000 --> 11:36.000
I could see four cows waiting patiently by the gate.

11:36.000 --> 11:37.000
And in another,

11:37.000 --> 11:40.000
there were some goats and a donkey.

11:40.000 --> 11:41.000
We are home.

11:41.000 --> 11:43.000
Said Uncle Fraser.

11:43.000 --> 11:46.000
Welcome to White Heather Cottage.

